      "demo.redhat.com/info-message-template": "{\"outputFormat\":\"html\",\"template\":\"ifndef::openshift_console_url[]\\n[%autowidth.stretch,width=40%,cols=\\\"^.^a\\\"]\\n|===\\n| Thank you for your patience! OpenShift access details will be available very soon after the service is successfully deployed.\\n|===\\nendif::[]\\n\\nifdef::openshift_console_url[]\\n=== OpenShift Console Access\\n\\nYour OpenShift cluster console is available at: +\\n{openshift_console_url}\\n\\nAdministrator login is available with:\\n\\n*User:* kubeadmin +\\n*Password:* {openshift_kubeadmin_password}\\n\\n=== Bastion Access\\n\\nA RHEL bastion host is available with common utilities pre-installed and OpenShift command line access pre-configured.\\nFor SSH access to the bastion:\\n\\n*Hostname:* {bastion_public_hostname} +\\n*User:* {bastion_ssh_user_name} +\\n*Password:* {bastion_ssh_password}\\n\\n.Example bastion SSH command\\n[subs=attributes+]\\n----\\nssh {bastion_ssh_user_name}@{bastion_public_hostname}\\n----\\n\\n=== API and Command Line Access\\n\\nThe OpenShift API is available at: +\\n{openshift_api_url}\\n\\nThe `oc` command line utility is available for download at: +\\n{openshift_client_download_url}\\n\\nA service account with cluster-admin access has been configured on your cluster and may be accessed with the following authentication token:\\n\\n.OpenShift API Token\\n[subs=attributes+]\\n----\\n{openshift_cluster_admin_token}\\n----\\n\\nYour OpenShift API is secured with the following TLS certificate authority.\\nFor secure access we recommend copying the certificate content to a local file, ex: `ocp-{guid}.ca.crt`.\\n\\n.OpenShift API CA Certificate\\n[subs=attributes+]\\n----\\n{openshift_api_ca_cert}\\n----\\n\\nIf you have saved your cluster CA certificate content to `ocp-{guid}.ca.crt` then you may log into your cluster using:\\n\\n.OpenShift command line login command\\n[subs=attributes+]\\n----\\noc login --server={openshift_api_url} --token={openshift_cluster_admin_token} --certificate-authority=ocp-{guid}.ca.crt\\n----\\nendif::[]\\n\",\"templateFormat\":\"asciidoc\"}",
